A new version of the [[Wikitext]] gem, version 1.6, is now available. This is a minor feature and maintenance release ([http://wikitext.rubyforge.org/files/doc/RELEASE-NOTES.html release notes]).

[[Wikitext]] is a fast wikitext-to-[[HTML]] translator with a syntax very close to that used by [[MediaWiki]]. It is a [[Ruby]] extension written with speed and robustness in mind using a [[Ragel]]-generated scanner and a hand-coded parser, all in [[C]]. It has an enormous spec suite.

You can browse the source code repo [http://git.wincent.com/wikitext.git here], or download the [[gem]] from the [[RubyForge]] [http://rubyforge.org/frs/?group_id=5483 downloads page]. For an overview check out the [[RDoc]] [http://wikitext.rubyforge.org/ here]. If you have [[RubyGems]] then you can install it with `sudo gem install wikitext`.

